title: Average weekly working hours in Sweden 2019 , by type of employment
yAxis: Average number of working hours per week
summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Average number of working hours per week for 4 number of Form of Employments.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
The lowest value at Form of Employment Temporary employed is 1.39x times less than the highest value at Self-employed.
min_summary: This bar chart has 4 columns on the x axis representing Form of Employment, and Average number of working hours per week in each Form of Employment on the y axis.
The Average number of working hours per week is appeared to be the highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Average number of working hours per week for 4 number of Form of Employments.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
The maximum Form of Employment Self-employed has got 1.39 times higher Average number of working hours per week than the minimum Form of Employment Temporary employed.

The Form of Employment Self-employed has the highest Average number of working hours per week, followed by Permanently employed, and Employed total. Down to the Form of Employment Temporary employed which is the lowest.
The Form of Employment Temporary employed has 1.17 times less Average number of working hours per week than average.
The Average number of working hours per week is 121.5 if we add up values of all Form of Employments.
